data.title: In its largest accession ceremony to date, NATO invited Bulgaria, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia to sign the North Atlantic Treaty during a meeting in Washington, D.C., Mar
data.text:
In its largest accession ceremony to date, NATO invited Bulgaria, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia to sign the North Atlantic Treaty during a meeting in Washington, D.C., March 29, 2005. Left to right: Slovenian Prime Minister Anton Rop; Slovakian Prime Minister Milkulas Dzurinda; Romanian Prime Minister Adrian Nastase; Lithuanian Prime Minister Algirdas Brazaukas; Latvian Prime Minister Indulis Emsis; Estonian Prime Minister Juhan Parts; and Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg Gotha prepare to speak to the press after the accession ceremony.
